# BetLab Backend

- Backend runtime is Node.js + Express (CommonJS).
- Server entrypoint is `backend/src/server.js`.
- Express app setup belongs in `backend/src/app.js`.
- Maintain backend process docs in `docs/backend-process.md`.

# Routing Conventions

- Mount all API endpoints under `/api`.
- Keep route modules in `backend/src/routes`.
- Keep a simple health endpoint at `/api/health`.

# Middleware Conventions

- Keep middleware in `backend/src/middleware`.
- Use centralized not-found and error-handler middleware.
- Return JSON errors using `{ ok: false, error: "<message>" }`.
- Log unexpected 5xx errors in the centralized error handler.

# Environment Conventions

- Keep local environment template in `backend/.env.example`.
- Expected vars:
  - `PORT`
  - `CORS_ORIGIN`
  - `MONGO_DB_URI` (or `mongo_db_uri`)
  - `BASKETBALL_MODEL_RESULTS_DIR` (optional override)
  - `BASKETBALL_MODEL_STATS_DIR` (optional override)

# Round Leader Projection Conventions

- PGA schedule picker data is cached in `backend/data/round-leader-projection-events.json`.
- Read cached schedule events via `GET /api/tools/round-leader-projection/events`.
- Refresh and overwrite cached schedule events via `POST /api/tools/round-leader-projection/events/refresh`.
- Projection requests accept `selectedStats` so users can define custom stat groups.
- Supported stat keys: `course_hole_model`, `par3_scoring_avg`, `par4_scoring_avg`, `par5_scoring_avg`, `sg_total`, `sg_t2g`, `sg_ott`, `sg_app`, `sg_arg`, `sg_putt`.
- If `sg_total` is selected, reject any payload that includes other SG keys to avoid redundant SG stacking.
- Cache stat snapshots by `tournamentId + currentRound + sorted(selectedStats)` in `backend/data/round-leader-projection-stats-cache.json`.
